```lean
theorem RelInt.liftFinf_in' {S} {rule : RelInt S} {n : Nat} {f : Fin n → List (RelInt S)}:
  (∃ (i : Fin n) (j : Fin (f i).length), rule = (f i).get j) →
  rule ∈ (RelInt.liftFinf n f) := by
  intro ⟨i, j, Hij⟩
  rw [Hij]
  unfold liftFinf
  simp only [RelInt, List.get_eq_getElem, List.mem_flatten, List.mem_map]
  -- We need to find a list in the image of f such that rule is in that list
  -- Given i and j, we have that rule is the j-th element of f i
  -- So, we need to show that the j-th element of f i is in the flattened map of f
  -- This is straightforward since the j-th element of f i is in f i, and f i is in the image of f
  exists (f i)
  <;> simp_all [List.mem_map]
  <;> aesop
```

